A small burgundy handbook submerged halfway out of the sand catches your eye. The cover reads, "Roadwarden Field Journal."

Day 434: Two days after leaving the Roadwarden path and striking out into the desert, I found an oasis in the Ankh'remun. A tribe lives here, and they seem very peaceful, eerily peaceful. After explaining that I am here to establish safe travelling routes, they warned me not to venture east of the oasis. Warring asabi nomads dominate the Valley of the Seven Sisters of Hoet. The Seven Sisters were giants who came from the mountains many generations ago to fight Asabini, which they say is a monstrous lizard that turned the giant sisters into stone! I must plot a course through this valley. They tried to talk me out of it, but I wouldn't be swayed. They gave me a sack of mushrooms they grow here, saying it wil make my dangerous journey more peaceful.

Day 436: Two days and haven't seen a thing. Cannot even find my way back to the oasis, because the wind has moved the dunes. Am out of food and nearly out of water, but I've started eating the mushrooms.

Day 437(?): I think? Really thirsty, but I'll make it. Saw a beetle and a spider! It was amazing. So colorful. The beetle was wearing a cape made of rainbows. So deep. Had an epiphany, but I forgot what it was.

Day yellow: No more water just mushrooms but i feel great really at one with the universe man totally at peace i'll just wait here a while and see if it rains rain instead of rosebuds and green clouds

another day: im dying but its the best day of my life
